<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Script Tag</title>
    <!--<link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">-->
  </head>
  <body>
    <h2>The html script tag</h2>
    <p>We use the script tag to create a JavaScript code inside the html document.</p>
    <p>Common uses for JavaScript are image manipulation, form validation, and dynamic changes of content.</p>
    <button onclick="myFunc()">Click to display text</button>
    <button onclick="myFunc1()">Click to change fontsize</button>
    <button onclick="myFunc2()">Click to change color</button>
    <button onclick="myFunc3()">Click to remove text</button>
    <p id="motor"></p>
    <script src="script.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>

